('chunk_4986214f24da969f19','file_fddb398b50b775766b','00-IB-framework-reference.md','1. What the MYP is (in one paragraph)','The Middle Years Programme (MYP, ages 11–16 / Grades 6–10) is a concept-driven, inquiry-based curriculum framework from the International Baccalaureate. It does **not** prescribe content the way a national board does; instead it organises learning around **big transferable concepts**, frames each unit with a **Statement of Inquiry** and **inquiry questions**, situates learning in real-world **Global Contexts**, and assesses students against published **criteria (A–D)** rather than only right/wrong answers. Grade 7 sits in **MYP Year 2**.

---','{"what":1,"the":4,"myp":3,"one":1,"paragraph":1,"middle":1,"years":1,"programme":1,"ages":1,"grades":1,"concept":1,"driven":1,"inquiry":3,"based":1,"curriculum":1,"framework":1,"from":1,"international":1,"baccalaureate":1,"does":2,"not":1,"prescribe":1,"content":1,"way":1,"national":1,"board":1,"instead":1,"organises":1,"learning":2,"around":1,"big":1,"transferable":1,"concepts":1,"frames":1,"each":1,"unit":1,"with":1,"statement":1,"and":2,"questions":1,"situates":1,"real":1,"world":1,"global":1,"contexts":1,"assesses":1,"students":1,"against":1,"published":1,"criteria":1,"rather":1,"than":1,"only":1,"right":1,"wrong":1,"answers":1,"grade":1,"sits":1,"year":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_375691f7845eb2eecc','file_fddb398b50b775766b','00-IB-framework-reference.md','2. The 16 MYP Key Concepts (broad, cross-disciplinary "big ideas")','A Key Concept is a large, powerful idea that reaches across subjects and years. Every MYP unit is built on **one or more** Key Concepts.

| Key Concept | Plain-language meaning | Typical subjects |
|---|---|---|
| **Aesthetics** | Beauty, taste, and how we perceive art and design | Arts, Language & Literature |
| **Change** | How things become different over time | Sciences, History, Geography |
| **Communication** | Exchange/transfer of information, meaning, messages | Languages, Arts |
| **Communities** | Groups connected by shared features or purpose | Individuals & Societies |
| **Connections** | Links and relationships between things | All subjects |
| **Creativity** | Generating new ideas and considering things in new ways | Arts, Design |
| **Culture** | Learned, shared beliefs, values, and practices of a group | Languages, History |
| **Development** | Growth, progress, and evolution over time | Geography, PHE |
| **Form** | The features/structure of something — what it is | Sciences, Arts, Maths |
| **Global interactions** | How humans, environments, and systems connect worldwide | Geography, History |
| **Identity** | What makes a person or thing itself | Language & Lit, PHE |
| **Logic** | Reasoning, proof, valid steps | Mathematics, Sciences |
| **Perspective** | Point of view; the position from which something is seen | History, Arts, Language |
| **Relationships** | How things affect/connect to one another | Sciences, Maths |
| **Systems** | Sets of interacting/interdependent parts forming a whole | Sciences, Geography |
| **Time, place and space** | The where and when; absolute and relative location | History, Geography, Maths |

**How to use:** Pick the *one* Key Concept that a unit is truly about. Don''t stack all sixteen. In this KB each unit names its Key Concept explicitly.

