('chunk_71c9b7b1bea548a26c','file_fddb398b50b775766b','00-IB-framework-reference.md','11. How to read a subject file in this KB','Each subject file is ordered: **Subject overview → Unit → Sub-topic (chapter) → Concept-by-concept entries**. Concepts carry the scaffold above. Use the master **`00-index.md`** to jump to any subject.','{"how":1,"read":1,"subject":4,"file":2,"this":1,"each":1,"ordered":1,"overview":1,"unit":1,"sub":1,"topic":1,"chapter":1,"concept":2,"entries":1,"concepts":1,"carry":1,"the":2,"scaffold":1,"above":1,"use":1,"master":1,"index":1,"jump":1,"any":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_c964718d3cf7e734c7','file_fcd18e24135890ff64','00-index.md','IISH MYP Grade 7 — Master Knowledge Base Index (2026–2027)','> **What this is.** A concept-by-concept, unit-by-unit knowledge base built from the IISH MYP Grade 7 Syllabus Focus (2026–2027). It is designed to power an IB MYP teaching assistant that teaches for understanding, inquiry, and transfer — not memorization. Every subject file is structured **Subject overview → Unit → Sub-topic (chapter) → Concept entries**, and every concept carries a 5-level explanation scaffold, real-world examples, analogies, misconceptions, IB concept tags, and command-term questions.
>
